From f87d3daddc9cfa183f3513fdbeeac822a49fa8dc Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Slick <slick@slicksync.local>
Date: Sat, 11 Jul 2026 20:17:12 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: require meaningful progress ratio for isActuallyWatched,
 show real avatars on Activity cards

isActuallyWatched()'s overallTimeWatched > 0 check was trivially true
for any nonzero Nuvio position, including a few seconds of hover/
preview autoplay while browsing the library (duration was never even
captured to compare against) - so saved-but-unwatched titles kept
reappearing as 'watched' activity despite the v1.9.3 fix.

getLibrary() now captures state.duration from the progress RPC.
isActuallyWatched requires progress >= 5% of runtime (AIOManager's
threshold) instead of any nonzero value, falling back to requiring a
video_id when duration is unavailable (live TV/IPTV).

Also threads avatarUrl/useGravatar through the recentActivity feed so
Activity cards show real user avatars instead of always falling back
to initials.

Bump to 1.9.6, changelog entry added.
